comments.body:
Doing some more reading, while the server side implementation is basically just for KDE, the client side implementation of this protocol is available in GTK 4.20;

The snap in the screenshot above was and still is using GTK 4.18 (it's likely to skip to 4.22 later this year). Debian is based on Gnome 48 and would also be using GTK 4.18.

It'd be worth testing this on Fedora KDE where assuming GTK4 4.20 is installed (bearing in mind Electron can also use GTK3), this functionality *might* work without any changes in the AppImage builds.
